The " pot-an-fen " is as much a national institution in France as is tea drinking among ourselves and it is prepared at least once a week in every bourgeois household. Thackeray, of course, waked enthusiastic about Bomillabaisse and sang - This Bomillabaisse a noble dish is, A sort of soup, or broth, or brew, A hotch-potch of all sorts of fiskes that Greenwich never could outdo ; Green herbs, red peppers, mussels, saffron, soles, onions, garlic, roach and dace.